      "source": [
        "# Problem Statement:\n",
        "**Breast Cancer Prediction Using Logistic Regression**\n",
        "\n",
        "Breast cancer is one of the most common types of cancer, and early diagnosis is crucial for effective treatment. The objective of this project is to build a Logistic Regression model to classify tumors as benign (non-cancerous) or malignant (cancerous) based on various cellular features. Using the Breast Cancer dataset from Scikit-Learn, we will perform data preprocessing, exploratory analysis, feature scaling, model training, and evaluation to ensure accurate predictions. The model will be assessed using accuracy, precision, recall, and a confusion matrix to determine its effectiveness in medical diagnostics.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "NtQOceuQl1zw"
      }

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import seaborn as sns\n",
        "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
        "from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, precision_score, recall_score, confusion_matrix, classification_report"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Ii_j_CJagpMh"
      },
      "execution_count": 3,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [

        "X = data.drop(columns=['target'])  # Features\n",

      "source": [
